      "strengths_deep_dive": [
        "MCN's financial health is characterized by its resilience and transparency. The organization has achieved a <cite id=\"10\">Platinum Seal of Transparency from Candid</cite>, the highest level available. Its governance structure is robust, featuring an <cite id=\"11\">83% independent board of directors</cite> and a <cite id=\"12\">100/100 score for Culture & Community</cite> from third-party evaluators. This institutional maturity is further evidenced by its <cite id=\"13\">3-year revenue CAGR of 10.9%</cite>, indicating steady growth and the ability to absorb increased funding for its <cite id=\"14\">youth leadership and civic engagement programs</cite>."
      ],
      "summary": "The Muslim Community Network (MCN) is a New York-based organization dedicated to <cite id=\"1\">shaping the public narrative about what it means to be Muslim in America</cite> through civic education and leadership development. Operating primarily within the <cite id=\"2\">five boroughs of New York City</cite>, MCN bridges the gap between the Muslim community and the broader public sphere. The organization manages a diverse portfolio of initiatives, including the <cite id=\"3\">MCN Impact Academy and a dedicated Zakat Fund</cite>. Financially, the organization demonstrates significant scale for its niche, reporting <cite id=\"4\">total revenue of $768,698</cite> in the 2023 tax year. MCN maintains a <cite id=\"5\">98/100 overall score from Charity Navigator</cite>, reflecting a high standard of institutional accountability. Beyond civic engagement, MCN provides direct community support through <cite id=\"6\">food drives, soup kitchens, and an immigration project</cite>, ensuring that its advocacy is grounded in tangible service delivery to vulnerable populations in the Bronx, Harlem, and Queens.",
